name: BBCWorld
text:
To win the election a candidate must win the majority of the electoral college

There are 538 of these state votes in total - whoever gets 270 votes will be president

It is still possible for both candidates to get to 270 and win the election

 https://t.co/RONqvm38UG https://t.co/qvC3RDegO8

name: BBCWorld
text:
The vote comes down to a few key states

Biden is projected to win Michigan and holds very narrow leads in Nevada and Arizona and some have projected a win for him in Wisconsin 

If he can hold on in these states he will get to 270 and the presidency

 https://t.co/RONqvm38UG https://t.co/vHa1MYTMhY

name: BBCWorld
text:
The most likely way for Trump to win is to take Pennsylvania and then 3 more of the remaining states - most likely Georgia, North Carolina, Nevada or Arizona  

But with votes left to count, and margins on a razor's edge, this could all change
  https://t.co/RONqvm38UG https://t.co/okBvGBh1lU

name: BBCWorld
text:
Both candidates have addressed supporters 

Biden urged patience but said: "We're going to win this" 

Trump said Republicans had won and claimed fraud

We know, votes are still being counted and there is no evidence of fraud

 https://t.co/RONqvm38UG https://t.co/ryYFwPjBiH

name: BBCWorld
text:
